      "notes": "For browning"
    },
    {
      "name": "1 tsp Ground Cumin",
      "amount": "1",
      "notes": "For flavor"
    },
    {
      "name": "1 tsp Smoked Paprika",
      "amount": "1",
      "notes": "For heat"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "In a large ceramic tagine, heat the Avocado oil over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped Onion and cook until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced Garlic and cook for an additional 1 minute.",
    "Add the diced Red Bell Pepper and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the mixed greens, diced Avocados, Nuka-pickle crumbs, Ground Cumin, and Smoked Paprika.",
    "Stir to combine and season with salt to taste.",
    "Transfer the tagine to the preheated oven and bake for 15-20 minutes.",
    "Remove from the oven and garnish with fresh herbs, if desired.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
  ],
